To create a simple fake chatbot using HTML and JavaScript, you can use the following code. This code will display a modal with a chat history containing 4 messages, 2 from the bot and 2 from the human user. You can customize the messages as needed.

HTML:
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Fake Chatbot</title>
    <style>
        .modal {
            display: none;
            position: fixed;
            z-index: 1;
            left: 0;
            top: 0;
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            overflow: auto;
            background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4);
        }
        .modal-content {
            background-color: #fefefe;
            margin: 15% auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #888;
            width: 80%;
        }
        .close {
            color: #aaa;
            float: right;
            font-size: 28px;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .close:hover,
        .close:focus {
            color: black;
            text-decoration: none;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <button onclick="openModal()">Open Modal</button>

    <div id="myModal" class="modal">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <span class="close" onclick="closeModal()">&times;</span>
            <h2>Chat History</h2>
            <div id="chatHistory">
                <div class="message">
                    <span class="user">Human:</span>
                    <span class="messageContent">Hello, how are you?</span>
                </div>
                <div class="message">
                    <span class="bot">Chatbot:</span>
                    <span class="messageContent">I'm great, thank you! How can I help you today?</span>
                </div>
                <div class="message">
                    <span class="user">Human:</span>
                    <span class="messageContent">I need some advice on programming.</span>
                </div>
                <div class="message">
                    <span class="bot">Chatbot:</span>
                    <span class="messageContent">Sure, I'd be happy to help. What do you need help with specifically?</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <script>
        function openModal() {
            document.getElementById("myModal").style.display = "block";
        }

        function closeModal() {
            document.getElementById("myModal").style.display = "none";
        }
    </script>
</body>
</html>
```
This code creates a modal that appears when you click the "Open Modal" button. The chat history is displayed within the modal, with alternating classes for the user and bot messages. You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see the fake chatbot in action.

